Description:
Adorable pink bouclé wool skirt by Chanel from the spring/summer ready-to-wear collection 1989.
 
Description
This A-line skirt features a high waist with a waistband, a concealed rear 19 cm - 7.5" zip with a hook fastening. The inside is fully lined with Chanel logo signed pink silk. It finishes above the knee. The style number on the label starts with P089 where 'P' stands for 'printemps/été' (spring/summer) and '089' for the year 1989.
 
Designer
Coco (Gabrielle) Chanel is famous for her timeless designs. She opened her first shop selling hats in Paris in 1910. In the 1920s she launched her first perfume, Chanel No. 5, and later in this decade the now legendary Chanel suits with boxy jackets and well-fitted skirts in pretty wools, tweeds and silks and the little black dress. Some years after her death Karl Lagerfeld became her successor as head designer in 1983. Since then he continues the Chanel legacy.
 
Condition
This skirt is in near mint vintage condition.
 
Size & Fit

Hips: 102 cm - 40.2"
Length: 47 cm - 18.5"
 
Measurements are taken flat and then doubled for waist and hips.

Product name: GUCCI "Flora" 1970s Vintage Silk Scarf Red Edging Vittorio Accornero
Description:
Iconic silk scarf from the 1970s by Gucci.
 
Description
This foulard features the legendary "Flora" motif print with nine multi-coloured bouquets of flowers from all four seasons with butterflies, beetles, a dragonfly and a grasshopper on an ivory background with red edging. It is made from silk twill, has hand-rolled edges and is signed "Gucci" and shows the artist's signature "V. Accornero" as well. The original care tag is still attached.
 
Designer 
Gucci was founded by Guccio Gucci (1881-1953) in Florence, Italy, in the early 1920s as a small family-run luggage company. Together with his sons, Gucci expanded his company selling fine hand-crafted leather accessories as well as silks and knitwear featuring his signature double G logo. By the 1960s Gucci's sons opened shops around the world and made the Gucci name synonymous with celebrity and chic. Gucci products quickly became internationally renowned for their distinctive style and turned into status symbols. They were valued by film stars and the international jet set such as Jacqueline Kennedy.
The iconic "Flora" print dates back to 1966 when Princess Grace of Monaco visited the Gucci shop in Via Monte Napoleone in Milan, Italy. Rodolfo Gucci wanted to gift her a special present and commissioned artist Vittorio Accornero to design a floral pattern for an original silk foulard. Today, it is one of Gucci's most timeless and storied motifs.
 
Condition
This scarf is in excellent vintage condition with very slight signs of use (few faint spots).
 
Measurements
87 x 87 cm - 34.3" x 34.3"

Product name: 1lb Dried Burdock Root
Description:
This listing is for 1lb of dried burdock root.
 
1lb is equal to about 5 cups.
Botanical Name: Articum Lappa
About Burdock Root
As a plant, the burdock is present all over Asia and Europe. As it normally grows along streets and fences it is simple to discover. In Asia the plant is picked while it is very young as a root vegetable. It is sweet tasting and the consistency is gummy. It’s full of calcium, chlorogenic acid, flavonoids, iron, inulin, lactone, mucilage, polyacetylenes, potassium, resin, tannin, and taraxosterol.
Conventional Uses of Burdock Root
In some alternative medicine the burdock plant’s seeds were compressed to create a mix that offered relief for measles, arthritis, tonsillitis, throat discomfort, and viruses such as the common cold. Burdock root may also be used to handle psoriasis, rheumatism, ulcers, acne, eczema, and gout. Some herbalists use it to handle snake bites and rabies. Dried burdock was also used by them as a diaphoretic, to purify the blood, and as a diuretic. The blood is purified by it by eliminating harmful toxins.
Treatment for Scalp Difficulties
The burdock root oil infusion, or Bur oil, can be found in Europe as a scalp therapy to prevent hair loss and assist with dandruff. It’s also believed to boost hair strength, glow, and increase hair growth by keeping a scalp healthy. It is believed to do this because the burdock oil has a lot of fatty acids and phytosterols.
Burn Therapy
The burdock plant’s leaves may be utilized for pain management and also to help accelerate the time that it takes burn patients to recover. As a barrier against dampness it’s believed to impede bacterial development and functions.
Cancer Benefits
Now, burdock root can be utilized in oncology for its cancer – treating properties, especially in India and Russia. Many natural remedy enthusiasts say that the burdock root can actually cease cancer cells from metastasizing. Research into the herb’s benefits has shown that burdock root has specific protective qualities that might describe its ability to help with cancer.
Helps to Lower Blood Sugar
Medline Plus, a site from the National Institutes of Health, states that animal study and the first human studies demonstrate that blood sugar can be lowered by burdock. It suggests that the herb has potential for treating diabetes, even though there isn’t yet enough study done into this particular aspect.
Safeguarding the Liver
There was proof that burdock root potentially aids in relieving liver injuries due to contact with carbon tetrachloride or acetominophen. It is theorized that it does this because of the compounds in the herb.

To replace the ink, pull off the top casing while holding the bottom casing and pull, then unscrew the pen cartridge. The pen cartridge is a standard cross type refill. The refill can be purchased from any office supply store. 
                                               HISTORY OF BLUE THIN LINE
The Thin Blue Line is a symbol used by Law Enforcement in the  United States and Canada to commemorate fallen officers and to symbolize the relationship of the police in the community as the  protectors of the citizenry from the criminal element.
Each stripe on the emblem represents certain aspects: the blue center line represents Law Enforcement, the top black stripe represents the public. The bottom represents the criminals. The thin blue line represents the thin line Police Officers walk daily between life and death.

What are "domed" overlays?  They are vinyl overlays with a top clear coat of polyurethane, making them thicker and more durable than NON domed (flat vinyl overlays).  The poly coat also gives them a glossy and 3 dimensional appearance. 
***FITS ALL SERIES OF SIERRAS: 1500, 2500, 3500, DENALI, ETC.***
*Please make sure you read description on the dropdown.  Make sure you order the grill and tail separately.  Front and rear overlays are NOT the same size and are NOT interchangeable.
This is your ONE-STOP SHOPPING for all sizes and colors! Unlike many other sellers, we ONLY make pre-cut emblem overlays, ready to install with NO TRIMMING NECESSARY!! Why would you want to risk using a sharp knife on your ride??
NOTES: 
***** IF YOU NEED BOTH, PLEASE MAKE SURE TO ADD EACH ITEM TO YOUR CART!!
-***Please be sure to select the right SIZE for your year! Both front and rear emblems are DIFFERENT from 2007-2013 and from 2014- current.** 
If you have a 2007 Sierra "Classic", please select the 1999-2006 model years from our store on another listing (this is because you do not have the current body style). 
These emblem overlays look great on just about ANY smooth surface!. Please be sure they will fit your vehicle before buying! Any questions, please ask!
These are self-adhesive, domed , flexible, vinyl *OVERLAYS* that are designed to install over your factory GMC emblems- the factory emblems are NOT included- sorry!
How hard are these to install? Not hard at ALL! Why? Because this very high-tech, specialty vinyl allows you to position the overlay and then lift it back up if you need to- again and again- until you apply pressure and make it "permanent"! Install them DRY with no worries!! When you want to remove it- simply heat it up (hair dryer works fine if you do not have a heat gun) and peel it off. AND it's removable up to 4yrs without leaving any residue or adhesive behind!
We even pre-mask these with clear transfer tape for even easier positioning!
Durable, dimensionally stable, vinyl film with positionable, pressure activated adhesive (permanent, changeable or removable) that allows it to be repositioned on the application surface during installation. Special channels allow trapped air to escape, which reduces air bubbles that typically occur as large format graphics are installed.

Product name: Baby's Breath Flower Crown - Dried Baby's Breath, Gypsophila, Boho Flower Crown, Dried Flowers, White Flower Crown, Baby's Breath Crown
Description:
This flower crown is made with dried baby's breath (gypsophila) and cream, silk blossoms. We dry our baby's breath in our studio, which allows us to make sure there is a perfect mix of open and closed buds in every batch. The baby's breath is intricately placed throughout the entire flower crown to create a romantic and beautiful headpiece. Perfect for weddings, photo shoots, and other special occasions. Because the flowers are dried, they are somewhat fragile; but, if taken care of properly, you'll be able to wear this crown over and over again! To keep your crown looking "fresh" longer, avoid contact with water, hairspray, and other elements that might damage the delicate blossoms. Look through our shop to see pictures of how other brides have styled our silk flower crowns for their big day! 
Flower selection and color, as well as stem wrap selection and color, can be customized upon request. We offer cream lace, natural burlap, burlap & lace, or any color(s) satin. If you have something different in mind, just send us a message. We love custom orders!
Coordinating bridal bouquets, bridesmaid bouquets, toss bouquets, boutonnieres, corsages, flower crowns, flower girl accessories, and décor can be made to order. Please message us for details.
Please check our shop policies or our shop announcement for current production times. If you are in a rush, please send us a message, or check out our ready to ship section here:

View our shop policies, current production times, and shipping information here:

Why Buy Silk Flowers?
Silk flowers are available year-round in almost any color, size, and style that you prefer. They are more durable than real flowers and can handle the craziness that often accompanies a wedding celebration. With silk flowers, you will know exactly what you are getting before it ever arrives, you'll get more for your money, and you won't have to worry about your flowers wilting or fading throughout the day. Besides, who doesn't love the idea of being able to keep their wedding bouquet forever?
Why Choose Blue Orchid Creations?
We carefully select each of our flowers to ensure that they are of the highest quality and are committed to creating unique pieces that are full of personality. We enjoy working with each of our brides to ensure that they receive the bouquet of their dreams – a bouquet they absolutely love. We understand that choosing flowers for your wedding is a big decision, and we want to make sure it is an exciting, enjoyable, and fun part of your wedding planning experience. 
How Do Custom Orders Work?
If you don't find something you love in our shop, send us a message so that we can discuss your custom order! We will respond as quickly as possible – always within 24 hours.

Now you can become an instant master coffee artist thanks to these clever coffee stencils. Each of the 16 attractive designs will allow you to express your creativity simply and easily, turning you into an instant expert coffee/latte artist!
